+Let me also check the events and test files to understand the expected behavior:  Now I understand all the bugs. Let me fix them:   Now let me run the tests to see the current status and understand what remains:                  All 34 tests pass. Here's a summary of the 6 bugs fixed:
+
+| File | Bug | Fix |
+|------|-----|-----|
+| `billing/calculator.ts` | Rounding intermediate values caused precision errors | Calculate raw values first, round only at output |
+| `billing/service.ts:25` | `handleRefund` not bound to `this` | Added `.bind(this)` |
+| `orders/repository.ts:38` | Update didn't preserve existing fields | Spread `existing` before `updates` |
+| `orders/service.ts:99` | `>=` rejected refunds on day 30 | Changed to `>` |
+| `orders/service.ts:75-83` | CANCELLED event missing `status` field | Added `status: 'cancelled'` |
+| `events/bus.ts:4` | Module-level handlers caused test pollution | Made handlers instance-level |
